history.p: Nielsen composed Fynsk Foraar during an enforced break from the work on the Fifth Symphony (CNW 29) during summer 1921. Pressure of time and failing health forced him to ask his pupil Nancy Dalberg to lend a helping hand with the instrumentation and the fair-copying.
